                    Section: 7 - Shipping, Taxes and Payments
1 - What we do here?
A quick overview of the section

2 - Shipping
Only relevant for physical product shops
You may need to do a lot of research on shipping costs for 
 - Various Countries
 - Various carriers
 - Weights
 - Other tarrifs

Shopify has different automation options available
 - Semi-Automated - Shopify will bring shipping costs etc in to the store but you will do labelling etc
 - Fully-Automated - 3rd Party will do all, known as dropshipping
 
No best one to use it will depend on the shop
Start up may begin by doing everything manually and when possible automate

Go to Settings -> Shipping
 - You can link store with shipping carriers
 - You will need an account with carrier which you will add
 - You can use existing or add new shipping zones with appropriate rates
 - Different rates for price, weights etc

3 - Payment Settings
Multiple Payment settings are available
 - Bogus Gateway -- Use for testing your site payments
 - Credit Card
 - PayPal
 - Shopify Payments
 - Manual Payments

Bogus Gateway has mulptiple options available for testing payments both from vendor and client view
PayPal - Has an express checkout option
You must have a proper account to use PayPal payments
Starting out you may be better off using Shopify Payments if available
Manual Payments can be customised

4 - Taxes
Different types of taxes
Shopify does not offer assistance on taxes related to business profits
Shopify does allow sales tax (VAT) to be added to goods
Each country will have different rules so you will need to seek professional advice
Recommended to leave sales tax box checked as you would have to pay it
Advice is also going to be needed on whether you can charge shipping tax

5 - Checkout Settings
Settings -> Checkout
Checkout has a number of options for fine tuning checkout settings
Style can be very important as it can improve conversion rates
Banner and Logos images can be added
Changes using images & logos can be previewed on the right hand side of the page
If not using images you can change colours
Ensure that the checkout maintains consistency with other parts of the site
Customer Acounts has 3 options
 - Accounts are disabled -- Customers will only be able to checkout as guests
 - Accounts are optional -- Customers will have the option to create an account at the end of the checkout process
 - Accounts are required -- Customers will only be able to checkout if they have an account
Option will depend on the shop and the products
You can enable multipass
Form has multiple options
 - Full Name
 - Company Name etc
Order Processing
 - Use Shipping Address as Billing Address by default
 - Add Confirmation step
 - Can set reminder if customer abandons cart
 - Ask for permission for promotional emails
After and order has been paid
 - Do not automatically fulfill any of the line items (unless you have automated system)
After an order has been fullfilled and paid 
 - You can automatically archive the order
 - You can also add custom scripts here
You can set checkout language
Refund, Privacy, Terms of Service policy
 - You can write manually or use Shopify to generate and then tune
Remember to save changes
 


                    Section: 8 - Apps for your Store
1 - General Overview of App’s
A quick intro to apps 
Shopify has its own App Store
Apps are bits of software that can add to the functionality of your store
There are a large amount of apps covering many different areas
There are bothe Free and Paid Apps
Just click the get button to install

2 - Things to watch out for
Avoid apps that are not supported wherever possible
Some apps may try and modify your existing setup again it may be better to look at an alternative

3 - App Ideas
You can add apps which will allow customers to add reviews
There is also a set of loyalty programmes apps available
You may want to intall a security app which will give you a trust mark
Mailchimp app available for email marketing
Installing Facebook app will allow you to use Facebook page to advertise



                    Section: 9 - Monitoring Store Financial Performance
1 - Financial Performance vs Bookkeeping
Shopify makes a comprehensive set of reports available for monitoring financial performance
 - Sales
 - Acquisition
 - Behaviour
 - Customers
These are all important to manage financial performance
Shopify does not include bookkeeping reports or services as standard however some can be integrated

2 - Monitoring Basic Financial Performance - How to
Report Dimensions can add fields to report & export as csv
Demo of performance using a spreadsheet eg Google Spreadsheets
You will need to seek professionaal advice on bookeeping practices

3 - Bookkeeping - The options

4 - Recap - Knowing when to Seek Advice



